</div> 
<p><strong>Blasphemous Blade</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatswords" href="/Greatswords" target="">Greatsword</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Blasphemous Blade</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> and is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;that deals additional fire damage.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Sacred sword of Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy.<br>Remains of the countless heroes he has devoured writhe upon the<br>surface of this blade.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Now they share the same blood, bound together as family.<br>Some HP is restored upon defeating an enemy.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Blasphemous Blade in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Blasphemous Blade weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Trade <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Blasphemous" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Blasphemous" target="">Remembrance of the Blasphemous</a> with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia" target="">Enia</a> at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Blasphemous Blade Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Taker's Flames" href="/Taker's+Flames" target="">Taker's Flames</a></li> 
 <li>Blasphemous Blade cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Blasphemous Blade cannot be enchanted using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations">Incantations</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Blasphemous Blade</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Heals 4% of max HP + 40 flat HP on every enemy death when held, whether or not this sword killed them.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Taker's Flames" href="/Taker's+Flames">Taker's Flames</a> Heals 10% of max HP + 150 flat HP on hit.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Taker's Flames" href="/Taker's+Flames">Taker's Flames</a> deals pure fire damage and only scales with faith.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Taker's Flames" href="/Taker's+Flames">Taker's Flames</a> can heal <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mimic Tear Ashes" href="/Mimic+Tear+Ashes">Mimic Tear Ashes</a> when the Blasphemous Blade is wielded by the&nbsp;Spirit Ashes.</li> 
 <li>Healing effect stacks with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greathorn Hammer" href="/Greathorn+Hammer">Greathorn Hammer</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Serpent-God's Curved Sword" href="/Serpent-God's+Curved+Sword">Serpent-God's Curved Sword</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard's Great Rune" href="/Rykard's+Great+Rune">Rykard's Great Rune</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Taker's Cameo" href="/Taker's+Cameo">Taker's Cameo</a>.</li> 
 <li>Pairs well with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sword of Milos" href="/Sword+of+Milos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sword of Milos</a> for a defense debuff on enemies, added Bleed damage, and FP recovery on slain foes.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
