				<li id="16787896" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1666056594000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578167/Blasphemous-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 Oct 2022 21:29</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16787896" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">My favorite weapon in the game. And you can get it within about 2-3 hours of starting the game. The only struggle is beating the Godskin in Volcano Manor. <br/>1. Get Dectus medallion half from Fort Haight.<br/>2. Take teleporter in Limgrave to Bestial Sanctum.<br/>3. Ride to Fort Faroth and grab other half of medallion (and the Soreseal while you are here). Just run past everything don&apos;t fight. <br/>4. Take shortcut around Stormveil into Liurnia.<br/>5. Complete Rya&apos;s quest (obtain necklace from Crab Guy, get invitation to Volcano Manor from Rya).<br/>6. Ride Dectus Lift. Talk to Rya and she will teleport you to VM.<br/>7. Get key and run through VM dungeon. The only tricky part is beating the Godskin boss, use spirit ashes or summons if you need to.<br/>8. Continue to Rykard, use the Serpent Hunter to defeat Rykard. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16787896" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16787896" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyp