				<li id="16737805" class="cmnt-root" data="-19" data-d="1657940438000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578167/Blasphemous-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">15 Jul 2022 23:00</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16737805" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This sword is not bad in PvP. If you have at least 80 poise, which you should on any decent PvP build, then you can easily poise through dex weapons and smash them for a winning trade every single time. Heavy armor also raises your robustness, which slows down RoB bleed spam, so that you can actually eat the first rotation and one shot them with takers flame. If you&apos;re locking on to use the weapon art, then you&apos;re doing it wrong. Run around a corner and then free aim takers flame as they follow. Unless they have ridiculous fire resistance or 60+ vigor, then they&apos;re all getting one-shot. I invaded into an instant 3 man gank, only for me to run around a corner and kill all 3 of them with taker&apos;s flame free aimed. Seeing as two of their summons had engame gear and weapons, they were most likely extremely high-level summons scaled down, and they still died instantly.<br/><br/>There&apos;s a reason why Giant Dad was the slayer of all dex users, and this is a direct upgrade to his weapon, thanks to the extreme range and AOE you can get on it. If you can get two of these and powerstance them with full jump attack damage boost from chest and talisman, then you can absolutely torch someone with just a single jumping L1. I only use 1 and I still smack people around like they&apos;re my tinder date.<br/><br/>The one thing you guys complaining about greatswords are lacking is spacing. If you don&apos;t space, then of course you&apos;re going to get obliterated by some powerstancing katana user, but hit for hit, you will far outdamage them to the point of the fight being completely one-sided.<br/><br/>I rock Alexander&apos;s shard, Ritual Sword Talisman, Fires scorpion charm, and then select Ritual Shield Talisman if I&apos;m getting one-shot consistently and want to stop dying, The FP skill reduction talisman for more uses, or just another pure damage talisman like the jump attack talisman to help burst harder. Fire scorp talisman is nerfed in PvP, so you can always drop it and go for Milicent&apos;s prosthesis, if you&apos;re an irredeemable twinky monster, or rotten winged insignia if you are a decent human being.<br/><br/>If you&apos;re low level twinking and you aren&apos;t skilled enough at the game to beat Fire Giant at level 20-40, then you can always kill Alexander for a nerfed version of Alexander&apos;s shard. In my opinion though, you should just get good instead. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16737805" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16737805" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>25</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16737805"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristin