				<li id="16725942" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1656464499000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578167/Blasphemous-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">28 Jun 2022 21:01</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16725942" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Wow, this is overpowered! I did testing with it against the stagecoach trolls in Limgrave, ignoring the first hit which has a bonus.<br/><br/>Skill damage:<br/>400 at +0 with 22 faith (R1 was 118 for comparison)<br/>489 at +0 with 61 faith<br/>564 at +2 with 22 faith (R1 was 194)<br/>604 at +2 with 32 faith<br/>620 at +2 with 61 faith<br/>1202 at +7 with 61 faith<br/><br/>By contrast, the Ruins Greatsword did only 247 damage at +0 and 917 damage at +9. Maybe these trolls have a fire vulnerability but still, that&apos;s insane damage, and it also heals you a huge amount per HIT, not per death, so it works on bosses. <br/><br/>Range seemed to be a *tiny* bit shorter than the Ruins Greatsword, but it was nearly the same. Of course this does low damage against fire-resistant enemies but overall it&apos;s just ridiculous. Also it&apos;s a greatsword, not a colossal sword, so it swings much faster one-handed and is lighter, with low requirements. Ruins does however knock down every non-colossal enemy not outright killed by it.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16725942" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="gl